news.title: Residential property prices in Germany fall by 5.7% in Q1 2024
news.para: High financing and construction costs continue to weigh on Europe's biggest economy, triggering the most severe property crisis in the country in decades.

news.title: Walplast Products invests Rs 300 crore in capacity expansion
news.para: These new plants located in Gujarat, Maharashtra, Madhya Pradesh and Andhra Pradesh will enhance Walplast's capacities for White, Grey and Gypsum products by 8,00,000 metric tons (MT) annually.

news.title: Kerala government to withdraw notification for acquiring land for Sabarimala airport
news.para: ​​​The government has also told the court that it will conduct a fresh Social Impact Assessment (SIA) study with regard to the project through a different agency.

news.title: Madras HC restrains Tamil Nadu government from evicting SRM Hotel
news.para: Justice G R Swaminathan, slamming officials for barging into the property on June 14 and taking possession of the property, the 30-year lease period for which had lapsed.

news.title: Telangana government exploring possibilities for the expansion of Hyderabad
news.para: Chief minister A Revanth Reddy in March had asked the municipal administration department to work out the expansion plans of the city civic body in view of rapid development in Greater Hyderabad.

news.title: Bombay HC berates man for defaulting on flat upkeep fees
news.para: Vilas Dongare challenged the dismissal of his complaint by Maharashtra Human Rights Commission that found no merit in his allegations regarding human rights violation.

news.title: Over 300 homes in Goa get go-ahead for rooftop solar panels
news.para: Govt had conducted a study and prepared a detailed project report (DPR) for the installation of rooftop solar power plants on govt buildings and also ground mounted solar power plant on govt land.

news.title: Act in land demarcation case or face action: Panchkula DC to officials
news.para: In his complaint, Gopal Singh said that two years ago the court had ordered demarcation of his land and despite court orders, the patwari-kanungo (revenue officers) did not address his complaint.

news.title: Bihar cabinet gives approval to metro projects in four more cities
news.para: The state cabinet approved the Urban Development and Housing Department's proposal pertaining to metro rail projects in Muzaffarpur, Gaya, Darbhanga and Bhagalpur.

news.title: Real estate sector sees debt sanctions of Rs 9.63 lakh crore during 2018-23: Report
news.para: The total debt market has a potential of Rs 14,00,000 crore (USD 170 billion) financing opportunity in Indian Real Estate between 2024-2026," the consultant said.

news.title: Consultants to submit Hyderabad's master plan by December 2024
news.para: Chief minister A Revanth Reddy had a few months ago announced that a comprehensive master plan-2050 would be prepared for the metropolitan region development for the next 25 years.

news.title: Daibiru Corporation invests Rs 1,000 crore in Gurugram building
news.para: This investment facilitated the exit of Abu Dhabi Investment Authority (ADIA), with Hines holding a 33% stake in the joint venture. The project, named Atrium Place, spans 2.88 million square feet across 11.76 acres and is slated for completion in 2025.

news.title: Common JVPD plots belong to 14 housing societies, not Mhada: Bombay HC
news.para: Justice Bharati Dangre’s order early this week said Mhada has no right, title or interest in these plots after execution of the registered common plot conveyance along with individual plot conveyances was done in favour of the 14 societies.

news.title: No proposal to monetize 25,000 acres of land around Bengaluru: Karnataka government
news.para: The focus of the Government is steadfastly on ensuring equitable economic growth so that poorer section of the society also accrue some benefits of rapid economic growth that the state is witnessing.

news.title: YEIDA likely to propose that builders bear all costs related to common area
news.para: Most group housing projects in YEIDA area are incomplete because the Authority needs to collect Rs 4,000 crore from developers in total.

news.title: Tamil Nadu registration department installs fingerprint scanners to combat fraud
news.para: All 582 sub-registrar offices in the state now have fingerprint scanner facilities, and the buyer-seller’s biometrics will be matched against the one-crore-plus sample data bank they have.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CM visits Amaravati, promises white paper on the capital city
news.para: ​Amaravati capital city project came to a standstill for five-long years from 2019 to 2024 under the YS Jagan Mohan Reddy-led YSRCP government. However, the change in government breathed life into the capital city project.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body cancels allotment of eight Indirapuram plots
news.para: The allotment, which took place in 2003, was carried out under the supervision of the then development authority secretary, Shyam Singh Yadav.

news.title: ED raids Amtek Group premises in over Rs 20,000-crore bank fraud case
news.para: ​The raids are being carried out on the Amtek Group and its directors, including Arvind Dham, Gautam Malhotra and others. About 35 business and residential premises in Delhi, Gurugram, Noida, Mumbai and Nagpur are being raided since this morning, the sources said.

news.title: About 65% of survey of dangerous buildings complete: Delhi civic body
news.para: According to MCD officials, the action was taken after issuing prior notices and providing adequate time to the owners or occupiers to demolish the buildings for safety reasons.
